2026-06-01 | Minimum Cost to Buy All Candies With Discount

	Question
Return the minimum cost required to buy all candies.
	Key Insight
To maximize discount:
		make the most expensive candies
		part of the purchased pair
and get the next expensive candy free.
So after sorting in descending order:
		buy first candy
		buy second candy
		get third candy free
repeat.
Example:
		[6,5,4,3,2,1]
		buy 6,5
		free 4
		buy 3,2
		free 1
		total = 6+5+3+2 = 16
	Approach
1.	Sort array in descending order.
2.	Process candies in groups of 3.
3.	Add cost of first two candies.
4.	Skip the third candy
		(it becomes free).
5.	If fewer than 3 candies remain,
		pay for all remaining candies.
	Time Complexity
	O(n log n)
	Space Complexity
	O(1) excluding sorting space
	Solution
class Solution {
public:
    int minimumCost(vector<int>& cost) {
        sort(cost.begin(), cost.end(), greater<int>());
        int ans = 0;
        for(int i = 0; i < cost.size(); i++) {
            if(i % 3 != 2) {
                ans += cost[i];
            }
        }
        return ans;
    }
};
	Key Insight
After sorting in descending order, every third candy can be taken for free. To maximize savings, the free candy should be the most expensive candy that can legally be made free, which naturally happens when we skip every third candy in the sorted order.
